item.title: Very weird compiler error
item.dc:creator: @Javacisnotrecognized _^_
item.description:
@Javacisnotrecognized wrote:

Well, when something is declared ‘abstract’, like update() in Player, what it leaves is an incomplete expression for a subclass to define more clearly. You need to define a method update() that has the same argcast as the method defined in Player
